caption: The tots and the wings were good, would recommend getting them again.  Ramen broth was lacking in flavor in my opinion though. I left with a desire to eat instant ramen.
Had a good experience in this place with my wife. The food was served quickly and the service is just good. Prices are reasonable.

We enjoy hanging out. Yesterday we went to this delicious restaurant which friends told us about. We spent a beautiful experience there with excellent food and a nice crew and  a professional  chef. We  added this venue in our phone list  and we will certainly come back very soon. We deeply recommend.
the store is nice, the employees are awesome and even their food is great
Good food abs great service. Ramen is delicious. The wings were so delicious. If you like crispy wings, order them... staff was very warm and welcoming.
Kimchi ramen was fantastic
Very disappointed in delivery.  The ramen broth was room temperature.  The items in it were cold. 2 stars since it was tasty.
Great meal to have for this very cold winter. It's delicious!!!

So, so delicious. One of my favorite ramen spots in town, and a nice sake selection too! When dining in was an option it was often packed, but the hosts always did a great job managing expectations and trying to keep everyone comfortable while we waited. Food was always worth the wait!
This food is amazing. Amazing. Such a comfort and a treat, warming and rich. Sitting outside, chilly fall evening, the crispy brussels and kimchi ramen were perfect. So so good.

At the first moment  you arrive in this place  they give you a nice feeling. Very courteous team, it is a lovely place to hang out with friends and colleagues or with your date. Great  food, specialist  chef de cuisine, competitive  cost and excellent  service. Warmly recommended.
The food and service were above our expectations. I surely liked the atmosphere of this spot. Superb place to take my family out for dinner.
(Translated by Google) A very nice place  (Original) Un lugar muy agradable
This place has amazing service and delightful meals. One of my favourite spots around here. The drinks and food arrived quick and the prices are fair. I recommend this place.
We had a great  at this spot. We liked the wonderful atmosphere and the meals. The waiters were super personal. I am happy we ultimately managed to try this place.

I’ve dined in and ordered delivery many times and their food always hits! I swear the miso ramen (+ pickled ginger) will heal your mind, body, and SOUL! They package the noodles and broth separately to preserve overall quality and deliveries are always spill-free. The shrimp and pork buns are both delish. And holy hell ya’ll their chicken wings are so crispy/crunchy and meaty.  Also recommend the beef gyudon!
Awesome ambience and very attentive service. The meals were crisp and delicious. Will definitely recommend this spot to friends. Affordable prices and big portions. Great work.

I eat a lot of ramen, and this one tasted good; strong flavors, good noodles, soy sauce egg was sweet and delicious, and the pork was awesome. The problem was they served it to me lukewarm. I ate it right in front of the place and it got cold in minutes. Disappointing for a $20 bowl (after adding ingredients). I also didn't love the kimchi, but I might just not like kimchi. The broth it came in was still delicious... just cold. A can of beer was also 9$. Frankly, I wouldn’t recommend this place over Danbo, Ichiran, ipppudo, kogane, nakamura, or many others.
Even their take out experience is amazing! Best Ramen anywhere. Hands up and down!

People giving this place great scores must not really know their ramen... The plates are very overpriced ($15 for the broth, scallions, carrots, and cabbage) then add ons like pork and bamboo are $1.00-$1.50 each. So that’s about $18 for a miso ramen that is extremely subpar. I’ve had better quality ramen for a better price in Manhattan. Disappointed and would not recommend 👎🏻

It's a bit of a wait, so make sure to plan accordingly! About 25 minutes around 4 on a Sunday. The ramen is absolutely delicious! The only downside is the amount of noodles you are given. Make sure to order extra. Service is a little spotty too, it seemed as though they were understaffed for the amount of volume.
Would certainly recommend trying this spot. Awesome vibes, yummy dishes, excellent customer service. Keep up the good work.

They told us it’d be a wait of 40 minutes, but we ended up waiting for a table for over 80 minutes. This delay totally screwed up our plans for the rest of the evening. Not worth the wait, go somewhere else and dont ruin your night here. The ramen was also average.
Love this restaurant the soup is amazing love it
Like Ramen? This is the place to go in Brooklyn: food is fresh, quality is there which make all Ramen are tasty.

I only eat vegetarian ramen and this was a pleasant surprise. I really liked the miso ramen, while my husband enjoyed his soy ramen. We also liked the tots as the snack ( could have a little less bonito flakes ).
Good place. Service could be a little better. Overall good experience. Recommended.

Vegan ramen!!!!! Finally I can come back to my favorite spot. The broth :10 the noodles:10 the service:10!!! Got seated super quick and my food came quick also <3 literally sang “I Love Yous” to my bowl. :)

Great local ramen spot! Usually busy on most nights, so definitely try and get a reservation. The ramen is rich in flavor, but not too greasy. I recommend getting the chicken wings/karage and/or roasted brusell sprouts.
Had a excellent experience in this spot with my girlfriend. The food was served quick and the customer service is just excellent. Prices are reasonable.

The ramen here was fantastic. Its seaweed base broth with chicken and poached egg proved to be comparable to Chinatown in Washington DC which is my favorite place for ramen. I'm not a pork consumer so the only way option I had was sweaweed base and it was fantastic.

Not sure why this place has so many 5-star reviews. Note that the base ramen is $15, and if you want anything on it (meat, eggs, or other stuff that's in the pictures), you have to get that extra. For this price, I expect some good stuff. The ramen we got was supremely unremarkable.

People's hyping this place up a lot. I notice it's mostly none Asian people who eat here so they probably haven't tried enough variety to compare. I ate at a lot of different ramen places in my life, and I'm telling you this is average. If you want some delicious ramen, I know a dozen better places. They still got 4 stars off me because it's the only place in the area that serves ramen, and the service was good. It's actually a 3.5 rating for me but can't put 3.5 so 4.

Used to have big head but food top knotch. We went on a ramen tour of NY and this place still best aside from Ramen Ya in village and that place on Henry St in BK. Specialty is the kale salad believe it or not. Spicy miso ramen bomb.
Had such an incredible well rounded dining experience.. fantastic staff, great drink and most importantly delicious food!
Hearty and filling bowls with lots of options. Fills up fast so get there early to make sure you get a table quickly.

This restaurant is doubtless one of the most attractive restaurants in the region. Anytime I come to this place I am highly glad. They keep their very high  standard service and the topmost level of cooking  they provide. You always win with this place. Very  recommended.
Pretty weird spaghetti but tastes good

Good Garlic Sesame ramen with roasted pork along with tots and great atmosphere!  First restaurant in New York and the experience was so professional and the staff are very timely I'd highly recommended to anyone looking for a quiet lunch spot.

Nice ramen restaurant but its not fully authentic. Stuff was priced well and was good but it's not a legitimate Japanese experience. Was a good dinner but not something I would remember. Slightly cramped inside.
Average Noodle place.  Waitress with bit of attitude as well.  Tall, thin unfriendly
Good Ramen

Everything was perfect: a not too long wait, great waiter, and food came out quick.  But ultimately the broth was incredibly over salted to the point where I had to take sips of water in between my slurps and chews of ramen. I got sick afterwards and have been all night now. Sad to say but think this ramen spot is a pass for me.

My second time there. First on a Saturday. A long line outside before their opening at 5:30pm. Excellent ramen (garlic sesame, kimchee). Quick/polite service. Music a bit loud. I would go back during the week.
Always amazing food and service
Tasty Ramen and great pork buns. Loved the chic and hip decor.

Chuko is great! Cozy and warmth space just like a ramen is when you eat it in the winter. They have different types of ramen and I tried the Miso one. Also, please have the Kale Salad, it is just unbelievable. They have also 3 types of sake you can have in a cup or in bottles of 300ml or 750ml. Otokoyama is definitely the best choice and it’s not the most expensive. Brooklin just got verter to me because of this place ☺️

This joint is where u love the decor, vibe, service is not bad and walked out feeling ripped off by the food. Part of being gripped by the hipster trend where you pay for everything you need to add to your ramen. I love the broth (garlic broth) but it comes with nothing but noodle, sliced wood ear mushrooms and scallion for a price I can have with a full bowl of ramen that includes the two slices of pork at most of the top rated ramen joints in the city or Brooklyn. Anyhoo, I can say I’ve tried, liked but will not come back again. Cheers.
Chuko means 'secondhand' in Japanese. I'm not overly impressed with the restaurant's other characteristics, either.
Ramen was good, place is very cool and the service is great!
Loovee this place,their ramen is delicious!
I will fight anyone who says anything against this perfect ramen and beer joint.

I came in here on a cold night in the middle of winter, and their ramen was the perfect antidote to the weather outside. Since then I've wanted to go back and enjoy the rest of the menu, as well as the sakes they offer, which compliment the saltiness and richness of the ramen.

Seriously - I’m lacking the words. After 1.5hrs wait what was supposed to be 45min, we got freezing cold ramen with one bowl 15$ for noodles and half pint soup, nothing else. The other bowl was 22$ with a bunch of extras, equally cold, they forgot half of it. The spicy garlic had no garlic. And... see the picture, this is chukos Interpretation of 3$’s worth of chashu pork, that isn’t even included in the 15$ base price. One. freaking. bite.  Your guys business practices are ridiculous.
The best ramen is vegan miso! Creamy and rich broth, amazing!
The food, service, decor and pristine conditions were all top notch. This place is special. Well done and thank you!
Great bowl - loved the spicy chili oil

Loved the layout and design of the restaurant. I enjoyed that there were traditional ramen flavor options, but also something different with the kimchi ramen option along with plenty of add-on options. The wings were amazing!
Regular
Food was amazing.. the pork bun was awesome.. just a bit said that the kimchee ramen wasnt spicy enough lol but overall great food
Very different and delicious menu. Loved this place. One visit is must when in Brooklyn.
Great simple ramen that doesn't need a million toppings because the broth is so good!

I'm so glad they added a second veggie ramen to their menu. We've been going to Chuko for years and it's always been some of the best ramen in NYC. Their sake list is also wonderful and the staff are very knowledgable and can make good recommendations based on your preferences. The new location is beautiful: very spacious and yet friendly.
Fantastic! Some of the best ramen you can find in NYC. Great atmosphere. Long line at busy times but worth the wait.
Best ramen I've ever had. Highly recommend.

Excellent service / ambience / best ramen this area. Great vegetarian options.  We ordered delivery through Caviar (1 Soy, 1 Kimchi Ramen), and it was the best delivery ramen we've ordered. It arrived separated in containers, refrigerator cold (broth in one, noodles & toppings in another), which was annoying at first (we didn't want to wash dishes, which was the point of getting takeout), but ultimately made the dishes travel really well and be delicious. SO I do highly recommend for delivery, but know that you will have to get a pot dirty.
Excellent ramen and lots of vegetarian options! Super friendly bartenders and servers
Food was quite delicious and place was wonderful.

The service here is rude. My father and I stopped in for dinner. We ordered our food and then noticed the table next to us who arrived after us received their ramen first. When my father followed up, the waitress said it's because we ordered appetizers. I don't mind the explanation, it was in the condescending and rude manner in which we said it. The ramen itself is just ok. I recommend avoiding this location.
Kimchee ramen with spicy pork and chili sauce! And don't miss the gyoza.

I am really disappointed. I remember coming here when they first opened numerous times with friends and colleagues. It was a no brainer to come here for lunch today. Oh my god! How disappointing it was. Wish I made a different choice. They charge extra for the sides that usually come with ramen. Every ramen restaurant I’ve been to in New York and around the world never charge you extra for the things that are supposed to come with a good bowl of ramen. The miso was salty as hell. My advice have a large bottle of water handy. This restaurant is dead to me. If you want Authentic ramen there are a bunch of great options. Choose wisely.

as good as you've heard
Great bowl of Ramen.

Used to be good, used to be reasonably priced but the new location and new menu have turned a worthwhile destination place into an overpriced disappointment. Every little thing is an upcharge and in the end it’s just not that good. A group of us revisited Chuko’s after loving the old location for some time and none bothered to finish their meal. Not worth it anymore.
A fantastic experience. Some of the best broth I've ever had. Fast and friendly service. They're not stingy with the noodles. They can also make everything vegetarian on request. Highly recommend.
They changed their menu and now it’s not as good as before, check out Ten-Ichi on 7th ave
The ramen is good. The gyoza were great.
Beautiful place! Great staff and amazing food!! Will highly reccomend.
Expensive and underwhelming.
I’ve been many times at Chuko but yesterday be made an appointment for 6 and everyone there was extremely helpful and nice to us. Love the people who works there, love the food, love the place.
Gotta try the pork buns!!!! 🔥🔥🔥 great food, great service

The ramen is decent but it was disappointing for the price. The ramen is more expensive here than a lot of better places that I've been to. I wouldn't recommend going out of your way for this but if you're in the neighborhood then it's not a bad option.
What a wonderful location. They offer a good variety of foods - at affordable prices.
Used to be very good. I thought it was meh recently. Probably won’t go back.

Quality used to be great, price was reasonable. However, now with the new menu, the base broth costs 14 without meat or veggies, and each add on costs 1.5. The broth and noodle aren’t particularly great either, small portion, too salty, lack personality. I have never been to a ramen restaurant that doesn’t have meat included (unless the ramen place is super good with quality noodle and broth). Chuko doesn’t have that. Very disappointed.
The cold ramen was just right on a hot summer day...
I love coming with my family. The food is great as well as the service. My 3 year old fell and dropped his noodles. They graciously provided him with another bowl of noodles for free.

This is a good place to have a dinner i have been there a couple of times with my friends and ones on a birthday party. The food is good and the service that they provide is okey for the price. Ones they messed up our order and i am giving you 3 starts because of the manager who didn`t do anything about it.

I hate waiting, but waiting for this ramen is worth it. Honestly, waiting for just the wings is worth it. If you go when they open the line is manageable. Sometimes we just order and assemble it at home. Either way, it’s worth it.
My first time eating ramen— great experience!
Great ramen and good service, friendly staff.. highly recommended!
Food was good. Great spot for a group. A bit overpriced.

(Translated by Google) My first Ramen 🍜, but I think I can say that it was impressively good .. good service, good atmosphere and adequate price quality  (Original) Mi primer Ramen 🍜, pero creo que puedo decir que era impresionantemente bueno.. buen servicio, buen ambiente y calidad precio adecuado

My first time had me hooked. First things first my waitress was pleasant and very informative she mad me feel like anything she suggested would be amazing and rightfully so as she suggested and I trusted her knowledge  the food arrived and I could wait to return to order more my money was definitely well spent

Craving some really good ramen when I was in town a few weeks ago, and went here with friends just after it opened on a Sunday. There was no wait at all around about 5:30, and the ramen itself came out quickly. It was really tasty, a good creamy broth with flavorful meat and a tender egg. It felt trendy but approachable, and the food made it extra worthy of a followup. I’ll be back next time I’m in New York!
Incredible ramen! If you're craving ramen go to Chuko in Brooklyn.   Pork buns, brussel sprouts and wings are all amazing... And I did the miso ramen with a poached egg and spicy ground pork 😍

Chicken wings are A+, however wrong food was run to the table and resulted in us eating the the table next to our’s while they watched(awkward) and then also gave us the wrong bill(which was more $). Also the place has a hipster Ramen vibe, if you prefer more classic style seek another place. The mix ups were really disheartening.
Overrated ramen...lacking in flavor (I ordered the miso)
Great place!!!

Perhaps I just prefer more traditional ramen. I always try to get it when I’m in New York but didn’t have time to go to manhattan. I have to say I left this place disappointed. I had the kimchi ramen. I never thought a broth would be too thick for me but this just was. And any meat or additional toppings are $1.50 so it ends up being more expensive than most other places as well.
Super Delish! I always ask for the curly yellow noodles no matter what broth I get, I’ve tried them all and they are the best texture. Also, Brussels Sprouts are amazing!!
I enjoy eating wings during my break time, very good and friendly staff

I would simply go here for the wings alone. Best wings I've EVER tasted in life. The food is amazing and the atmosphere is very enjoyable. Great place to eat good ramen. Go try the wings, it's worth it.
You want meat? That'll cost extra. Want an egg? That'll cost extra. Want your ramen spicy? That'll cost extra. Also menu doesn't match other location per your Google pages.

This restaurant is tried and true. The best Ramen in Brooklyn. I remember when it was much smaller and down the block. Spicy Miso is my favourite, but this is one of those places where every dish can satisfy you. They only do reservations for large groups. Just go in and they will let you know how long the wait will be or grab a bar stool. It's worth it.  Chuko is good for the soul.
Food was really good! Service was great!
Great place for awesome ramen. The broth was so tasty. Friendly staff and great service. Crispy brussel sprouts for appetizers way just right.
the ramen was good, but I felt for 14$ its ridiculous that it doesnt come with meat and you have to buy it. I feel that its standard to give at least one peice of meat.
It's nice place and good service, appetizers very good but the ramen wasn't how we expected
Yummy ramen in my tummy :)
Loved it
Overpriced, the egg is an ADD ON?? But otherwise ok
Best ramen in BK... Go for the soy soup base.
Great ramen. Only downside is that literally all the toppings if it's not indicated will cost extra.
First time, I enjoyed the food and the ambience.

My colleague and I had to attend an offsite training nearby and were looking to find something nearby to lunch and he googled and found this ramen place within 0.2 miles walking distance from where we were. We ordered two bowl of ramen, one soy ramen and one miso ramen. Surprisingly there were no meat (Japanese roasted pork or cha siu) to come with ramen and they somehow served as side order and cost $1.50 per a piece of roasted pork, and one pouched egg also cost another $1.50. The miso ramen used yellow original ramen noodle, with butternut squash and cabbage and not the usual ingredients used for Japanese Style ramen, the soup base was just fair. My colleague ordered a soy ramen with buck wheat noodle, scallion and nori, and he said it’s too oily for the soy ramen. He paid over $37.00 for 2 bowl of ramen for lunch and this is pricey for this neighborhood.
The food is incredible but it is expensive
So good. Went here while visiting and loved it. I was sad to get home and realize that ramen near me doesn't compare.
good ramen
The buns were amazing and the ramen was top notch.Tanya, the manager was really nice. Highly recommend
My son enjoyed his ramen
Good stuff 👌🏽
The wait took a while, but it ended up being worth it as the ramen here is absolutely delicious. You can't make a bad choice!
Delicious buns and salad! Limited drink offering but this place is gold!
Great miso ramen, also get the spicy garlic oil (rayu) with it.

Personal opinion, the ramen wasn't something to rave about. Note that this is a fusion/hip place, not an authentic Japanese ramen place. If you expect them to have great ramen, get ready to be disappointed. The ramen do not come with any meat by default, the roast pork is stiff and barely has any flavor. If you're going to this place, you're better off getting their appetizers. The best thing about this place was their chili oil though, very flavorful but it's not super spicy. But don't let my review discourage you from trying this place out, I suggest you make reservations as a walk in wait for me was 45 minutes.

My first impression of this place was "hmm it's cozy." I love the lighting and the music play lists were good. The space was diffidently small and I felt that it was hard for me to get out of my seat and scared that I would knock down things from other's table, especially during winter with big jackets. The service is alright.  They have a few signature ramenS. One of them is miso ramen- with cabbage and pumpkin in it, your order is the  basic then you need to add toppings which costs extra like around 1.5$?(not 100%sure) for a pouched egg  or a piece of roast pork. A bowl of ramen with meat and egg, easily goes up to about $20, not including the tax and tips. I think that was a little too much. If you only want to fix your ramen craving this is would be a bit on the luxury side. My friend and I went on a Sunday and it was snowing, the place was still packed. 30 minutes wait for two people. If they let you make reservation, definitely do so. After all, if you have the money to indulge, go for it! Solid ramen and a nice environment. Plus the neighborhood it's located in has great stores, vintage thrifting,  classic book store, and Ample Hills Creamery...a great day, ALL SET!

(Translated by Google) If you don't add a point, the ramen is completely unfinished. Later, I added some simmering eggs and pork, and I really didn’t have a good match with the soup.  (Original) 若不加點，拉麵是完全沒有配料的。後來加點了溏心蛋跟叉燒，說真的跟湯頭沒有很搭。
It's the best ramen in the neighborhood and maybe the best ramen in all of Brooklyn. You want this.
Over rated. Ramen in the city in Japan Town orders of magnitude better than this. Miyoso is so way better than this.

Amazing food! Very friendly staff. Excited to go back and try other things in the menu. Definitely worth the wait but I'd advise getting there very early because it fills up quickly. It's worth having a very early dinner for sure.
Best place in area for ramen. Brussels & kale great. Order add-ins for your ramen.
One of the best! It’s worth the wait! Get there before they open! Great for families.

Some great dishes and a solid ramen. One bummer, is that they price the bowls at just noodles only (e.g. $15 for a miso ramen). So you end up having to add the stuff  (like meat, egg, nori, bamboo) that should be standard with the bowl as extra at $1-2 an item. All in all you're looking at over $20 for a bowl of ramen, which just seems a little unreasonable. You'll get more for your buck at other ramen joints in the city.
Good ramen, although a bit expensive. Would appreciate a few more options on the menu too.
Great ramen and snacks. The tots and Brussels sprouts were fantastic.  Avoid the sake, especially the ‘panda’ and ‘ramen puppy’.  Seriously overpriced and terrible.  Service was good.
Had a nice miso ramen today.  Food is good but prices are a bit out of control.
It was pretty good and for those whom like sweet sake beware 19% alc will get you stupid. Otherwise the meal was fantastic I will be back.

So I’m a big ramen lover and I’d heard good things so I came to check it out. I wasn’t very impressed. The ramen is far from traditional, I got the garlic miso ramen and asked for a side of spicy paste. When added to the broth, it made everything way too salty and not very spicy. Also they make you select a base and then add your toppings so if you want pork and an egg you’re gonna be paying like $20 for the ramen. The noodles tasted a bit too much like spaghetti too. Wrong type of noodles of you ask me. Underwhelming for my tastes but I’m a bit picky
Great place to work and eat.

Rating it a 4 because 1)the pork buns were good, light and tasty 2) the place 3) the music 4) eh the service was okay.  There’s better ramen out there though for sure. Not worth the price. The ramen was not seasoned well.

Love this place.  Prices tend to be a bit higher then other good ramen places but this is our Brooklyn #1 ramen choice.  Get there by 5:20 if you want to definitely get in, otherwise be prepared to wait.
Love the Ramen served at this small welcoming restuarant. Definitely a spot worth checking out.
Great place to work and have some ramen noodles.
Excellent ramen restaurant. Excellent food and very friendly staff. Superb pork and shrimp buns

I'm a minority here, but it's just ok!!! Dry pork bun and meh ramen. Smells great in there!
Overpriced ramen .

Good. Bring the kids. Crowded so plan ahead

People complain about the price, but it's the best bowl of Ramen in this part of Brooklyn and maybe east of the East River. I can speak to the quality of the vegetable broths they use - very rich and full of umami. Their apps are great too - shrimp buns, kimchi are great. The wait can be annoying as they don't take reservations, but I've never had a bad meal here and service is always quick and on point. This is probably the restaurant I frequent most, to be honest!
Delicious ramen

As someone that has been a fan of Chuko since I first tried their ramen, I’ve become very disappointed. I’ve ordered their ramen countless times and have found the quality to decrease time after time. It’s honestly ridiculous to be paying $2 for the smallest, thinnest piece of roast pork, when most places come with it. I really tried to give this place a second chance by ordering again but am sad to say this will be my last time.
High quality ramen, exactly what you’d expect with great service
The vegetarian ramens are so full of flavor. Also, make sure to get the kale salad!
Ramen broth is really fantastic. Worth every min

Ramen doesn't come with an egg, meat, veggies. You buy ramen and pay extra for adding egg, meat, veggies. Almost $20 for a bowl. $7 for the cheapest beer and you started charging for that tiny garlic spice. The server came to me and rudely complained that I left only 10% tip. It's very rude and unprofessional to point it out to the customer. Anyway the service didn't deserve 20%, we had to catch another waitress to order more drinks. It was my favorite place, always went there and brought friends and family, now have to find a new place to eat ramen.
Good ramen but pretty pricey. Did not come with any toppings. Have to add on, $1-1.50 each.
The staff is extremely rude and unprofessional. The hours of operation are extremely odd. I encourage any sensible people to shop elsewhere.

Fantastic ramen joint, straightforward menu that always over delivers
Food is great but you can get more good Ramen for less e.g. at Zest
Chuko is overrated m, and both their service and food is lacking quality! You have to pay extra to get meat and veggie etc - It’s not like it used to be. There’s better Ramen places around.
Decent. Not sure why they charge extra for toppings.

Best ramen I have ever had by far and the sides are amazing as well. I would recommend the crispy brussel sprouts, kale salad, pork belly bun, and ANY ramen. They do take your phone number and text you when your table is almost ready though so you can go to one of the many local bars to wait, which is nice.
Really tasty! A bit pricy but worth it.

Simple menu but good quality ramen. I ordered the miso wth yellow noodles, an egg, fried tofu and a piece of meat as my additions. I went a weekday before their first closing at 3 and my main complaint was that the soup wasn't hot enough. Maybe coz they were about to close? Best Ramen in this part of town. Hostess Staff could be a little more friendly hence 4 stars.

People are crazy if they rate this less than 5 full stars.  I’ve been countless times to both locations and it never disappoints.  If you’re vegetarian - the thick miso ramen can not be beat - NO ONE does a veg ramen as good.
Really delicious Ramen!
Pretty neat, one of the better ramens! Excellent noodles. The pork slices are pretty thick, and just two slices of nori. My quest for an authentic Tokyo ramen continues, anyhow.
My waitress was amazing... Priya I beleive her name was... I didnt have thr best day but she was there with suggestions on food and choices and cheered me and my brother on...
Not the best I've had. The ramen is just broth and noodles... everything else you need to order separately. 5 Stars for staff though!

A Brooklyn staple for ramen. Whether you stick with the classics or try the monthly specials it's always worth the wait! I'd recommend going early (5:30/6) or late (9:30) to avoid the crowds. But I love eating here. Great place for friends, or large-ish groups (6-8)

I had the extremely rare opportunity to be in Brooklyn, near the Barclay's Center on Thursday, 3/22/18 around lunchtime, so I took that opportunity to try someplace new. I googled "food near me" and "best food in Brooklyn" and both times Chuko came up. Its only a few minute walk from the Barclay's so I decided to go check it out. When I arrived, it wasn't open yet because it was only 11:45am and they don't open until noon. It was very cold standing out front for 15 minutes and I was hoping they would open the doors a little early and let me in, but they didn't. Oh well, the food was worth the wait. I started off by ordering a steamed pork bun. It was definitely the best pork bun that I've ever had. The pork was a thick slab of soft and juicy pork belly, with pickled carrots and cucumbers and chili mayo on a soft and warm bao bun. Excellent!! For my ramen, I went with the pork bone broth, soft egg and roasted pork. I've only had ramen at two restaurants on Long Island, but this blew them both out of the water! The broth was amazing, there were a ton of noodles in the bowl, the mushrooms were flavorful, the egg was poached perfectly and the pork was more of the soft, tender, delicious, thick sliced pork belly that was also in the bun. My only complaint is that I wish there was more pork in the bowl! Getting into Brooklyn isn't easy, but is definitely worth it to go to Chuko! I can't wait to have the exact same order the next time I'm there!!
